727401f-b.text:
Metropolitan Avenue (right, telegraph pole thereon) at the
S.W. corner of Woodhaven Boulevard.  View No. 2 is looking south-
eastward from Metropolitan Avenue (tracks thereon). Views 3 and
4 are looking northward on Trotting Course Lane. This house,
sometimes known as the Garret Vanderveer house, was erected in 1850
by Henry [Suyden] Vanderveer.  In 1880 it was moved from its old
site, which was located opposite the old homestead, to the present
site and here enlarged and remodeled. For more data see views on
the north side of Metropolitan Avenue opposite Seventieth Avenue.
Other owners were C. Vanderveer in 1873.  J. Vanderveer in 1896,
and Jeronus Vanderveer's Estate in 1923. The house partially seen
at the left in view No. 4 is the Van Dine farmhouse.

April 1923
Views 1 and 4
View 2: 1922
View 3: March 1923

728214f-a.text:
Woodhaven Boulevard, at the southwest corner of Metropolitan Avenue, showing one of the Vanderveer houses, built in 1850.  This house was built on a site farther east on Metropolitan Avenue, and was removed to this location 1880.  Henry Suydam Vanderveer built the house.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

April, 1923
